title: For Sale:  8mm Gew.88 Mauser/Steyr Collectors Rifle 1890
postcontent: This one has history!  It's a Steyr Gewehr 88 from 1890, way before WWI when the German Empire still had a Kaiser (emperor) and looks to be having used in the fight with the Ottoman Empire (Persia, now Iran). It is also often erroneously referred to as “Mauser” or “Mannlicher”.  It has all the hallmarks and markings that make this a rifle to have, from the Emperor's crown to the Ottoman insignia.   Kaiser Wilhelm II was Germany's last emperor and this baby could have seen action in Iran, then the 1st World War, on to WWII.  The bore's rifling is still exceptional an the rifling twist is incredible, especially with this extra long barrel. Rounds chamber tight and the rifle works flawlessly, we shot 2 boxes and the accuracy is incredible! You can actually see those 8mm extra large bullets hit where they impact, even at a distance. Speaking of which, it has a flip up sight for long range shots. Whatever you hit with this baby, it's going down hard...  With the sight in regular mode, it is sighted to 273 yards, then you can flip it up and it's range is from 500 yards, with approx. 110 yard increments to a total range of 2187 yards.  5 shot clip, which can be strip loaded for fast reloading...  At 124 years of age this puppy will give most modern rifles a run for the money especially in accuracy, my buddy with his scoped rifle couldn't believe the distances that this will hit at, without even a scope.  REAL German quality, even after a 124 years, it becomes very apparent when shooting it.  While you can just hang it on your wall as a show off rife, it will be a real joy to shoot, take it hunting and show your buddies how it's done Old School...  You WILL NOT run across another one like, it is very rare...  Cash Only! $600 Or best Offer, will entertain all reasonable offers
